CS 6107 - COMPUTER NETWORKS
---------------------------

MODULE I PETERSON(1)
  Foundation:
    Applications, 
    Requirements, 
    Network Architecture, 
    Implementing Network Software, 
    Performance.

MODULE II PETERSON(2.1-2.5)
  Direct Link Networks: 
    Hardware Building Blocks, 
    Encoding (NRZ, NRZI, Manchester, 4B/5B), 
    Framing, 
    Error Detection, 
    Reliable Detection, 
    Reliable Transmission, 

MODULE III PETERSON(2.6-2.9)
  Ethernet (802.3), 
  Token Rings (802.5, FDDI), 
  Wireless (802.11), 
  Network adaptors.

MODULE IV PETERSON(4.1-4.3)
  Internetworking: 
    Simple Internetworking (IP),
    Routing, 
    Global Internet, 

MODULE V PETERSON(4.4-4.5)
  Multicast, 
  Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS).

MODULE VI PETERSON(5)
  End-to-End Protocols: 
    Simple Demultiplexer (UDP), 
    Reliable Byte Stream (TCP), 
    Remote Procedure Call.

MODULE VII PETERSON(6)
  Congestion Control and Resource Allocation: 
    Issues in Resource Allocation, 
    Queuing Disciplines, 
    TCP Congestion Control, 
    Congestion-Avoidance Mechanisms, 
    Quality of Service.

Text Book:
1. L.L. Peterson & B.S. Davie- Computer Networks: A Systems Approach, 3rd Edition, Morgan Kaufman Publication, New Delhi, 2006

Reference Books:
1. A. Forouzan -  Data communications and Networking, 4th Edn., TMH, New Delhi, 2006
2. P.C. Gupta- Data Communications and Computer Networks, PHI, New Delhi, 2006.
